This project has a graphify knowledge graph at `graphify-out/`.

Before architecture or codebase questions:
1. Read `graphify-out/GRAPH_REPORT.md` for god nodes and community structure
2. Or run CLI: `graphify query "..."`, `graphify explain "NodeName()"`, `graphify path "A" "B"`
3. If `graphify-out/wiki/index.md` exists, navigate it instead of reading raw files

After modifying code in this session → `graphify update .` (AST-only, no API cost).

Android build assets are excluded via `.graphifyignore` — query `src/`, not `android/app/src/main/assets/`.

Zustand stores often appear as thin/isolated communities; verify real usage via imports in source, not graph degree alone.
